  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Yes, we are all Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, if you are Jews then you must be friends of England because England has got the mandate over Palestine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And yeah, all us Jews want-- are Zionists and want to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The implication is that if you are friends of England, yeah, by implication, friends of an enemy-- the friend of an enemy is your enemy.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had to explain to these men [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how-- that some of his basic assumptions are somewhat farfetched.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And to tell him that first of all, the people who come here, Jewish politics is the last thing on their mind anyhow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They are concentrating on one purpose only, to keep body and soul together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If they pull through alive and in the reasonable health, they will have achieved the utmost that they can ever hope for to achieve under such depressing and-- and tragic circumstances.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for anybody to-- to-- to-- to get involved in politics, per se, is absurd [INAUDIBLE] here, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I said, if you want to know the sociology of Jewish-- of Jewish involvement in terms of political identification, Zionists those days were only a very small minority of people [INAUDIBLE] a majority of people among the Jews who were against Zionism, who were actively against Zionism, who didn't want-- the assimilationists didn't want to be identified as Jews, let alone as Zionists.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Bundists didn't want to be Zionists because they wanted to leave, and did dispersion, and that was their ideology.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you have got the wrong aspect of approach to the entire issue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it wasn't an easy way to persuade him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somehow I disengaged from them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I certainly didn't-- they didn't forget me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I certainly didn't forget them.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
